UNITED STATES v. AMERICAN NATIONAL BANK, a Corporation, Conservator of the Estate of Edward Anderson, Mental Incompetent. No. 89. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. August 9, 1929. George Stephan, ü. S. Atty., and Richard A. Toomey, Regional Atty. U. S. Veterans’ Bureau, both of Denver, Colo., for appellant. Kenaz Huffman and Luke Kavanaugh, both of Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before LEWIS, COTTERAL, and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Dismissed August 9,1929, on stipulation.
